    static class SpecificTesterClasses.DoubleToQuadTester
extends TesterClasses.Conversion_T2Q_Tester<Double>
    A tester class to test the conversion from double to Quadruple, namely the Quadruple.Quadruple(double) constructor.
    Obtains the test data from DataProviders.d2qConversionDataList() and performs Quadruple.Quadruple(double) as the tested operation.

      • findExpectedResult

        protected BigDecimal findExpectedResult(Quadruple operand)
        Calculates a BigDecimal value equal to the expected result of the conversion from double to Quadruple.
        The expected result is the exact value of the double, whose value is passed in as a Quadruple parameter, expressed as a BigDecimal. In cases of NaN, Infinity, and -Infinity, throws a NumberFormatException and further processing is performed by the parent class.
        Overrides:
        findExpectedResult in class TesterClasses.UnaryFunctionTester<Double,Quadruple>
        Parameters:
        operand - the value to be converted
        Returns:
        the expected result of the tested operation as a BigDecimal
